claim.claim-text:
1. A method of producing a radiation-emitting thin film
semiconductor chip, comprising the steps of:
growing a second active zone on a growth substrate;
growing a first active zone on the second active zone;
removing the first active zone in a second region;
detaching the entire growth substrate; and
removing the second active zone in a first region such that the first and second regions are separated from one another laterally by a space;
wherein the first and the second active zones are removed by etching;
wherein an etch stop layer is arranged between the first and second active zones, up to which the first active zone is etched away in the second region and the second active zone in the first region; and
wherein the second active zone in the first region is etched after flipping the thin film semiconductor chip around.
